            "body": "<p>No, there is no option to compile that right.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private JPanel b_,cb_,pb_,l_,tf_,ta_contentPane;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Is a correct sentence.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>b_,cb_,pb_,l_,tf_,ta_contentPane = new JPanel();\nb_,cb_,pb_,l_,tf_,ta_contentPane.setBorder(new EmptyBorder(5, 5, 5, 5));\nb_,cb_,pb_,l_,tf_,ta_contentPane.setLayout(new BorderLayout(0, 0));\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Are incorrect sencences.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 17095683,
            "question_id": 17095470
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/dc064a0af5b489a8a5aec8dcf53cc21e?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2109967,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1875434,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1875434/abbas",
                "reputation": 7219,
                "display_name": "abbas",
                "accept_rate": 67
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1371228035,
            "creation_date": 1371161312,
            "body": "<p>The code is correct but the variable name generated is a not a valid identifier. The solution is to rename the variable and the code will compile fine.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private JPanel contentPane;\n\npublic Mainf() {\n    contentPane = new JPanel();\n    contentPane.setBorder(new EmptyBorder(5, 5, 5, 5));\n    contentPane.setLayout(new BorderLayout(0, 0));\n    setContentPane(contentPane);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 17097997,
            "question_id": 17095470,
            "last_edit_date": 1371228035
        }
    ],
